---
import type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
export interface Props { font: CollectionEntry<'fonts'>['data']; }
const { font } = Astro.props;
const fam = font.fontFamily;
---
<div class="iu" style={`--fam:${fam}`}>

  <!-- 01 — READING APP: a shipped product, real device scale, interactive type panel -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">01</span><span class="label">Reading app — long-form at real scale (interactive)</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene">
      <div class="iu__device lrdr" data-lrdr>
        <div class="iu__chrome">
          <div class="iu__dots"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
          <span class="iu__addr">read.marginalia.app</span>
        </div>

        <div class="lrdr__top">
          <span class="lrdr__logo">Marginalia</span>
          <div class="lrdr__progress" aria-hidden="true"><i style="width:34%"></i></div>
          <button class="lrdr__aA" data-typetoggle aria-expanded="true" aria-label="Typography settings">
            <span class="lrdr__aAsmall">A</span><span class="lrdr__aAbig">A</span>
          </button>
        </div>

        <!-- typography settings popover (the interactive surface) -->
        <div class="lrdr__panel" data-panel>
          <div class="lrdr__prow">
            <span class="lrdr__plabel">Weight</span>
            <input type="range" data-waxis min="400" max="700" step="1" value="400" aria-label="Font weight" />
            <i class="lrdr__pval" data-wout>Regular</i>
          </div>
          <div class="lrdr__prow lrdr__prow--feats">
            <span class="lrdr__plabel">Detail</span>
            <div class="lrdr__chips">
              <button class="is-on" data-feat="liga" aria-pressed="true">Ligatures</button>
              <button data-feat="frac" aria-pressed="false">Fractions</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <article class="lrdr__body" data-text>
          <p class="lrdr__kicker">Essays &middot; The Reading Life</p>
          <h4 class="lrdr__head">The warmth of a brushed letter</h4>
          <p class="lrdr__byline">Oluwaseun Adeyemi &middot; <span class="lrdr__fig">14</span> June <span class="lrdr__fig">2026</span></p>
          <p class="lrdr__lede"><span class="lrdr__drop">T</span>here is a quality in certain typefaces — the ones drawn with a brush rather than ruled with a pen — that you feel before you can name it. The fi and fl ligatures close; the office of letters settles into a harmony; and the column acquires the warmth of something written, not composed.</p>
          <p>Lora carries that quality onto every screen it inhabits. Held at <span class="lrdr__fig">16</span> pixels, roughly <span class="lrdr__fig">3/4</span> the size of print, it keeps an even, inviting colour across a long measure. The serifs bracket firmly; the stress leans gently back toward the pen.</p>
          <blockquote class="lrdr__quote">A typeface drawn for the screen does not merely survive it; it belongs there.</blockquote>
          <p>The calligraphic root is never decorative. It is structural — those softened terminals are the reason a column of Lora reads like the work of a careful hand and not a typesetting engine.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">Tap <b>A</b> to open the type panel — drag the weight (400&ndash;700) and toggle ligatures &amp; fractions; the column reflows live, just like a real reading app.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 02 — LITERARY SPREAD: printed paper surface, bleed accent, drop cap, italic pull quote -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">02</span><span class="label">Literary spread — printed paper, drop cap, italic pull quote</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-lit">
      <div class="iu__poster lit" data-lit>
        <!-- verso: full-bleed accent page -->
        <section class="lit__verso">
          <span class="lit__kicker">Fiction &middot; Issue <span class="lit__num">23</span></span>
          <h3 class="lit__title">Every Letter<br/><em class="lit__ital">Written Twice</em></h3>
          <p class="lit__sub">A story about a correspondence that outlasted the correspondents — and the hand that held it together.</p>
          <span class="lit__author">Cécile Marchand</span>
        </section>
        <!-- recto: body text on cream paper, drop cap + pull quote -->
        <section class="lit__recto">
          <p class="lit__body"><span class="lit__drop">T</span>he letters arrived every Tuesday without fail, in envelopes the colour of old cream, the address written in a hand that had never entirely left school. Inside, the sentences were long and considered, full of parenthetical qualifications, the way a person writes when they have all afternoon and nobody to interrupt them.</p>
          <p class="lit__body">She kept them in a box under her writing desk, tied with a length of green ribbon she had cut from a hat she no longer wore — each one dated, each smelling faintly of the cedar drawer where the box had wintered.</p>
          <blockquote class="lit__pull"><em>The letter is the one form that waits for you. It does not refresh itself; it simply sits there, patient, until you are ready to read it again.</em></blockquote>
          <p class="lit__body">What surprised her, rereading them after he was gone, was how many were really about the act of writing itself — the pleasure of choosing a word, the small decisions of spacing and margin that constituted a kind of care.</p>
          <footer class="lit__foot">
            <span class="lit__folio">24</span>
            <span class="lit__mag">Meridian Review</span>
            <span class="lit__folio">25</span>
          </footer>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A two-page literary spread on toned paper — brushed drop cap, italic pull quote, and an even body colour at paragraph scale. The drop cap settles on load.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 03 — PUBLISHER BRAND: real wordmark lockup + catalogue with typographic rhythm -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">03</span><span class="label">Brand — literary publisher identity &amp; catalogue</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-brand">
      <div class="iu__poster brand" data-brand>
        <!-- left: identity lockup on accent surface -->
        <div class="brand__side brand__side--ident">
          <div class="brand__lockup">
            <span class="brand__est">Est. <span class="brand__fig">1987</span></span>
            <h3 class="brand__name">Meridian</h3>
            <svg class="brand__rule" viewBox="0 0 300 10" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" preserveAspectRatio="none">
              <line class="brand__line" x1="2" y1="5" x2="298" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4"/>
            </svg>
            <span class="brand__tag"><em>Independent Publishers</em></span>
          </div>
          <p class="brand__genres">Fiction &middot; Poetry &middot; Essays &middot; Translation</p>
          <dl class="brand__stats">
            <div><dd><span class="brand__fig">38</span></dd><dt>Years in print</dt></div>
            <div><dd><span class="brand__fig">1,248</span></dd><dt>Titles published</dt></div>
            <div><dd><span class="brand__fig">34</span></dd><dt>Languages</dt></div>
          </dl>
          <span class="brand__foot">meridian.press</span>
        </div>
        <!-- right: current season catalogue -->
        <div class="brand__side brand__side--cat">
          <span class="brand__season">Spring <span class="brand__fig">2026</span> &middot; New Titles</span>
          <ul class="brand__list">
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">01</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>The Cartographer&rsquo;s Widow</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Priya Nair &middot; Novel</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£14.99</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">02</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>Seventeen Letters</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Marco Calderón &middot; Stories</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£12.99</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">03</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>The Weight of Silence</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Yuki Tanaka &middot; Poetry</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£16.50</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">04</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>Archipelago</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Fatima Al-Rashid &middot; Essays</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£13.99</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="brand__note">Prices set in tabular figures — columns align regardless of digit width.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A publisher identity: a wordmark + rule lockup beside a season catalogue. Italic titles, tabular prices that align, and a rule that inks in on hover. Click a title to select it.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 04 — FEATURE OPENER: continuously breathing weight axis, asymmetric roman/italic tension -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">04</span><span class="label">Feature opener — weight-breathing headline, italic/roman interplay</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-open">
      <div class="iu__poster opener" data-opener>
        <div class="op__head">
          <span class="op__issue">Meridian Review</span>
          <span class="op__issue op__issue--r">No. <span class="op__num">23</span> &middot; Summer <span class="op__num">2026</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="op__center">
          <span class="op__over">A special feature on</span>
          <h3 class="op__title">
            <span class="op__l1">The Calligraphic</span>
            <em class="op__em" data-breather>Imagination</em>
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="op__bottom">
          <p class="op__stand">How a generation of designers gave the screen a letter shaped not by a ruler but by a brush — and what that warmth does to the act of reading.</p>
          <div class="op__foot">
            <span class="op__by">Essay by <em>Isabela Ferreira</em></span>
            <span class="op__pp">pp. <span class="op__num">12&ndash;21</span></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">The display italic <em>Imagination</em> breathes continuously across Lora&rsquo;s full weight range (400&ndash;700); hover to push it to bold and hold.</p>
  </figure>

</div>

<script>
  // ---- 01 READING APP: type panel — weight slider + feature toggles ----
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-lrdr]').forEach((rdr) => {
    const text = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-text]')!;
    const wout = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-wout]')!;
    const waxis = rdr.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('[data-waxis]')!;
    const panel = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-panel]')!;
    const toggle = rdr.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-typetoggle]')!;
    const state: Record<string, boolean> = { liga: true, frac: false };
    let wght = 400;

    const wname = (w: number) =>
      w < 450 ? 'Regular' : w < 550 ? 'Medium' : w < 650 ? 'SemiBold' : 'Bold';

    const apply = () => {
      const feats = `'liga' ${state.liga ? 1 : 0}, 'frac' ${state.frac ? 1 : 0}`;
      text.style.fontFeatureSettings = feats;
      text.style.fontVariationSettings = `'wght' ${wght}`;
    };

    toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const open = panel.hasAttribute('hidden');
      if (open) panel.removeAttribute('hidden'); else panel.setAttribute('hidden', '');
      toggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(open));
    });

    waxis.addEventListener('input', () => {
      wght = +waxis.value;
      wout.textContent = wname(wght);
      apply();
    });

    rdr.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-feat]').forEach((btn) => {
      const feat = btn.dataset.feat!;
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        state[feat] = !state[feat];
        btn.classList.toggle('is-on', state[feat]);
        btn.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(state[feat]));
        apply();
      });
    });

    apply();
  });

  // ---- 03 BRAND: SVG rule length + catalogue row selection ----
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-brand]').forEach((card) => {
    card.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-hover]').forEach((row) => {
      row.addEventListener('click', () => {
        card.querySelectorAll('[data-hover]').forEach(r => r.classList.remove('is-selected'));
        row.classList.add('is-selected');
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .iu__item { margin: 0; }
  .iu__hint { margin-top: var(--sp-2); color: var(--fg-3); }
  .iu__hint b { font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .iu__cap { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.7rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-2); }
  .iu__scene * { font-family: var(--fam); }

  /* shared scene framing */
  .iu__scene {
    container-type: inline-size;
    position: relative;
    border: clamp(22px, 3.4vw, 44px) solid var(--bg-2);
    outline: 1px solid var(--line);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--bg-2);
  }
  /* scene 01 is a fixed-height device; print scenes (02–04) size to content */
  .iu__scene:not(.scene-lit):not(.scene-brand):not(.scene-open) { aspect-ratio: 16 / 10; }
  .iu__device {
    position: absolute; inset: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    background: var(--bg); overflow: hidden;
  }
  .scene-lit > .iu__poster,
  .scene-brand > .iu__poster,
  .scene-open > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; width: 100%; }
  .iu__chrome {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg-2); flex: none;
  }
  .iu__dots { display: flex; gap: 6px; }
  .iu__dots i { width: 9px; height: 9px; border-radius: 50%; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fg) 20%, transparent); }
  .iu__addr {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--fg-3);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fg) 5%, transparent);
    border-radius: 6px; padding: 3px 12px; margin: 0 auto;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  /* ============================================================
     01 — READING APP (real px, interactive)
     ============================================================ */
  .lrdr {
    font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;
    --tint: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 4%, var(--bg));
    background: var(--tint);
  }

  .lrdr__top {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg); flex: none;
  }
  .lrdr__logo {
    font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg);
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600; letter-spacing: -0.01em; flex: none;
  }
  .lrdr__progress {
    flex: 1; height: 3px; border-radius: 3px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fg) 10%, transparent); overflow: hidden;
  }
  .lrdr__progress i { display: block; height: 100%; background: var(--accent); border-radius: 3px; }
  .lrdr__aA {
    flex: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 1px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 4px 10px; cursor: pointer; color: var(--fg-2);
    background: var(--bg); transition: border-color 0.18s var(--ease), color 0.18s var(--ease);
  }
  .lrdr__aA:hover { border-color: var(--fg-3); color: var(--fg); }
  .lrdr__aA[aria-expanded='true'] { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
  .lrdr__aAsmall { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; }
  .lrdr__aAbig { font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600; }

  .lrdr__panel {
    display: grid; gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--bg); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); flex: none;
  }
  .lrdr__prow { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.8rem; }
  .lrdr__plabel {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3); width: 4.5ch; flex: none;
  }
  .lrdr__prow input[type='range'] {
    -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; flex: 1;
    height: 2px; background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fg) 15%, transparent);
    border-radius: 2px; cursor: pointer;
  }
  .lrdr__prow input[type='range']::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none;
    width: 14px; height: 14px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent); border: 2px solid var(--bg);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--accent);
  }
  .lrdr__prow input[type='range']::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 14px; height: 14px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent); border: 2px solid var(--bg);
  }
  .lrdr__pval {
    font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; color: var(--accent);
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600; width: 8ch; flex: none; text-align: right;
  }
  .lrdr__chips { display: flex; gap: 0.4rem; }
  .lrdr__chips button {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    color: var(--fg-3); padding: 0.28rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 100px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line); cursor: pointer; background: var(--bg);
    transition: all 0.18s var(--ease); white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .lrdr__chips button:hover { color: var(--fg); border-color: var(--fg-3); }
  .lrdr__chips button.is-on {
    color: var(--accent-contrast); background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .lrdr__body {
    padding: clamp(1.4rem, 4cqi, 2.8rem) clamp(1.3rem, 5cqi, 3.6rem);
    max-width: 60ch; margin: 0 auto;
    overflow-y: auto; flex: 1 1 0; min-height: 0;
  }
  .lrdr__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
  }
  .lrdr__head {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4.4cqi, 36px); line-height: 1.08; margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--fg);
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600;
  }
  .lrdr__byline { font-size: 13px; color: var(--fg-3); font-style: italic; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
  .lrdr__fig { font-feature-settings: 'tnum' 1; font-style: normal; }
  .lrdr__lede, .lrdr__body p {
    font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--fg-2); margin: 0 0 1em;
  }
  .lrdr__lede { font-size: 17px; color: var(--fg); }
  .lrdr__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 3.1em; line-height: 0.74; padding: 0.04em 0.13em 0 0;
    color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; font-variation-settings: 'wght' 700;
  }
  .lrdr__quote {
    font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic; color: var(--fg);
    border-left: 2.5px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .lrdr__chips button, .lrdr__aA { transition: none; }
  }
  @container (max-width: 480px) {
    .lrdr__top { padding: 0.6rem 0.85rem; gap: 0.7rem; }
    .lrdr__panel { padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem; }
    .lrdr__prow input[type='range'] { min-width: 0; }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     02 — LITERARY SPREAD (printed paper surface)
     ============================================================ */
  .scene-lit { background: var(--bg-2); padding: clamp(8px, 2.2cqi, 26px); }
  .lit {
    --paper: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 6%, #fbf7ee);
    --ink: #221b12;
    color: var(--ink);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.15fr;
    container-type: inline-size;
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'kern' 1;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px -22px color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 60%, transparent),
                0 1px 0 color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 10%, transparent);
    position: relative;
  }
  /* gutter shadow between the two pages */
  .lit::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; bottom: 0; left: 46.5%;
    width: 7cqi; transform: translateX(-50%); pointer-events: none; z-index: 1;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg,
      transparent, color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 9%, transparent) 42%,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 13%, transparent) 50%,
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 9%, transparent) 58%, transparent);
  }
  .lit__verso, .lit__recto { padding: 6.5cqi 5.5cqi; }

  /* verso — full accent page */
  .lit__verso {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; gap: 3cqi;
    background: var(--accent); color: #fbf3e6;
  }
  .lit__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 2cqi; letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: color-mix(in srgb, #fbf3e6 80%, var(--accent));
  }
  .lit__num { font-feature-settings: 'tnum' 1; }
  .lit__title {
    font-size: 10cqi; line-height: 0.95; font-weight: 600; margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: #fbf3e6; font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600;
  }
  .lit__ital { font-style: italic; display: block; color: #fbf3e6; font-variation-settings: 'wght' 500; }
  .lit__sub {
    font-size: 2.7cqi; line-height: 1.5; font-style: italic;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, #fbf3e6 85%, var(--accent));
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, #fbf3e6 35%, transparent);
    padding-top: 3cqi; max-width: 32ch;
  }
  .lit__author {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1.9cqi; letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: color-mix(in srgb, #fbf3e6 75%, var(--accent));
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  /* recto — paper body */
  .lit__recto {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; background: var(--paper);
  }
  .lit__body {
    font-size: 2.45cqi; line-height: 1.62; color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 0.85em; text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: justify; hyphens: auto;
  }
  .lit__body:first-of-type { text-indent: 0; }
  .lit__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 10cqi; line-height: 0.72; padding: 0.4cqi 1.1cqi 0 0;
    color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; font-variation-settings: 'wght' 700;
  }
  .lit__pull {
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 18%, transparent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 18%, transparent);
    margin: 2.6cqi 0; padding: 2.4cqi 0;
    font-size: 3cqi; line-height: 1.42; color: var(--accent); font-style: normal;
    text-align: center; text-indent: 0;
  }
  .lit__pull em { font-style: italic; }
  .lit__foot {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink) 18%, transparent);
